
=Description=

"OneAim.org

is an international, independent and open meta network for committed individuals and organisations which want to mutually solve structural problems in the participation of the world population in social-political processes, civil society co-operation, the Internet and medial distribution of human visions of the future in an open dialogue.

Everyone is invited to participate because only those things which find support will be realised (see project ranking).

Important content is to be translated into 30 languages.

The following three – independent of each other – general dialogues with various sub-projects existing under OneAim.org apart from the translator’s network Language Without Borders will be currently presented:

1. World Social Web Dialogue
Structural improvements on the Internet for social action and free, decentralized infrastructures.

2. OneAim EU
Improvement of the participation and the co-operation within the EU.

3. OneAim Media Dialogue
Interactive TV and radio show; cross-website eco-social Internet commercial market for the distribution of human visions of the future, social entrepreneurship and social investment via the media."
(http://www.oneaim.org/)

